Ornelas, Staff / San Antonio Express-News Clemens, Baker outlast Smithson Valley 1 / 1 Back to Gallery About midway throught the fourth quarter of Fridayâ€™s neck-and-neck thriller between Clemens and Smithson Valley, Buffaloes Head Coach Jared Johnston told his team they were going for two if their offense had the ball last.
That view proved prophetic, as star Clemens quarterback Frank Harris hit Sanuel Kearns for a last-minute touchdown and then strolled into the endzone for the conversion to give the Buffaloes the 57-56 win.
